>
	<p>
		I am a software engineer with 6+ years of experience building user-facing and backend systems
		across fintech, analytics, and developer tooling. My work has ranged from cloud migration and
		payment services to Kubernetes-focused infrastructure, with a consistent focus on reliability,
		performance, and shipping useful products end to end.
	</p>

	<p>
		Most recently, I contributed to Layer5 as an open-source software engineer, working on Meshery
		and Kubernetes discovery flows. That work included streaming-list optimizations, operator and
		CRD improvements, test stabilization, and improvements to cluster resource synchronization. I
		also spent several years at Vantage Intellica and Tingle Software building data pipelines,
		internal tools, microservices, and production systems used by large active user bases.
	</p>

	<p>
		My technical toolkit includes Go, Python, C#, JavaScript, Kubernetes, Docker, AWS, Azure,
		PostgreSQL, Redis, and distributed messaging systems such as SQS and SNS. I enjoy the kind of
		engineering work where architecture, code quality, and operational behavior all matter at the
		same time.
	</p>

	<p>
		I recently completed an MSc in Artificial Intelligence with distinction at Nottingham Trent
		University. That academic work sharpened my interest in combining strong software engineering
		foundations with data-informed systems, especially where performance, memory efficiency, and
		product usefulness have to coexist.
	</p>

	<p>
		Outside of day-to-day delivery, I care about clear technical writing, maintainable systems, and
		tools that help teams move faster without losing confidence. This blog is a place to capture the
		practical ideas, experiments, and design decisions that come out of that work.
	</p>
